{
  "stem": "20686.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I said, Master, grant me a language, no, grant me the words of an illogical language, how fathers used to murder little children and ask the heavenly-- their god-- to bless their-- bless their work.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now all this sort of thing is very complicated.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, and, and therefore, I believe greatly in, in describing what took place in, in a epic form.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why in epic form?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because the metaphor which is used in poetry is not to embellish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's not to, to dramatize.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it's-- it is the magnifying glass through which one can see what really took place, that one can describe, even with the limited amount of, of language available to us.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the limitation of language stems from the fact, in my opinion, that what took place lies outside the logic of human beings.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the logic of-- a human being prepared language as he went alone in history, as we came from, from, from our-- the primordial stages till now.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We could describe.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We found adjectives and, and, and words to describe things which we were familiar with.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This is something we have-- we, we never experience.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In one of my-- I, I, I, I say here about-- in the 'Elegy on Ghetto,' I would like to talk-- tell about ghetto.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "'Is there a language for that?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How do you describe a child's plea silenced by death?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Or how do you explain a man's heart forced to witness his wife beaten, tormented, raped, buried alive?",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Or how do you tell of a hanging, one noose for father and son?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And soldiers stand about the gallows to enjoy the fun.' Now, where do you get this sort of language?",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
